name: Tachyons
comment:
[Tachyons](http://tachyons.io/) is an _the_ best CSS framework ever. It's an implementation of
what people call "Functional CSS" which, as an Elm programmer, need I say more?

In functional CSS you have a ton of little CSS classes that do one thing, and
do it well #unixphilosophy.

Essentially what this means is that can create almost any interface without
writing custom css, you only need to compose different CSS selectors together.
for instance you could do this using this library:

    div [classes [pa1, red, f1]] []

This will:
- Add the smallest padding available on all four sides (Padding Around 1)
- Make the foreground color red (an Accessible friendly version)
- Make the `font-size` as big as an h1 tag.

There's even responsive versions. Like `p1_ns` that will only have the padding
on anything that's "not small" (larger than mobile). This makes making responsive
interfaces really easy.

# Working example

This is the smallest possible program for working with this library.

    module Main exposing (..)

    import Tachyons exposing (..)
    import Html exposing (..)


    main =
        div [ classes [ f1, purple ] ]
            [ tachyons.css
            , text "I'm Purple and big!"
            ]
